'''Jean, Baron Stéphenne''' is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. He studied chemistry and bioindustries and obtained an [[Master of Science|MSc]] degree at the [[Faculté universitaire des sciences agronomiques de Gembloux]] in 1972 and an [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] degree from the [[Université Catholique de Louvain]] in 1982.
Jean Stéphenne joined [[SmithKline-RIT]] (now GlaxoSmithKline Biologicals) in 1974 as head of [[bacterial]] and [[virus|viral]] [[vaccine]]s production, he became ''Vaccine Production Director'' in 1980. From 1981 to 1991, he served as Vaccine Plant Director and R&D Director. From 1988 to 1991, he was Vice President of Human Vaccines Research and Development and Production. From 1991 to 1998 he led the vaccines division, first as Vice President and General Manager, then Senior Vice President and General Manager, until his appointment as President and General Manager in 1998. Since 1998, Jean Stéphenne is President and General Manager of [[GlaxoSmithKline Biologicals]].
In 2001, Stéphenne was raised into the [[Belgian nobility]] by [[Albert II of Belgium|King Albert II]] and given the noble title ''[[Baron]]'' for life.<ref>[http://www.ejustice.just.fgov.be/cgi/article_body.pl?language=nl&caller=summary&pub_date=01-07-19&numac=2001015079#top Publicatie : 2001-07-19, Numac : 2001015079] - [[Belgian official journal]]</ref>
Since 2013, Jean Stéphenne is shareholder and chairman of [[OncoDNA]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.biopark.be/oncodna-en.html|title=OncoDNA|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=|via=}}</ref>
