'''Luis Hernández Heres''' (born 24 August 1949) is a [[Cuba]]n former [[Association football|footballer]] who competed in the [[1976 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=sref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/he/luis-hernandez-heres-1.html |accessdate=7 June 2012}}</ref>
==International career== He represented his country in two games at the 1976 Summer Olympics.<ref>{{FIFA player|176296}}</ref>
==Football administration== Subsequently, he became a businessman and football administrator, and a member of the [[FIFA Council]], the main decision-making body of FIFA, the governing body of association football.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/committees/committee=1882019/ |title=FIFA Committees - FIFA Council |website=FIFA.com |date=2016-07-01 |accessdate=2016-08-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/concacaf/executive-committee |title=CONCACAF Council |website=Concacaf.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-22}}</ref>
Hernández was elected to the FIFA Council in May 2016, as one of three representatives of the Confederation of North, Central America and Caribbean Association Football ([[CONCACAF]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/concacaf-elects-new-president-and-members-of-concacaf-and-fifa-councils |title=CONCACAF Elects New President, and Members of CONCACAF and FIFA Councils |website=Concacaf.com |date=2016-05-12 |accessdate=2016-08-22}}</ref>
